      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done in PS8. Refactored PropertyInfo to hold a list of (interface, property name) targets so one propertyId can be written to multiple D-Bus interfaces. Added addPropertyTarget helper; the if/else block after the switch is removed; the response handler iterates targets instead of branching on propertyId.\n\nThe constructor registers the assembly asset interfaces as additional targets for SERIAL_NUMBER, MARKETING_NAME, DEVICE_PART_NUMBER, and BOARD_PART_NUMBER.\n\nSince this refactor modifies shared inventory code that predates this patch, verified on nvl32-obmc hardware that UUID, BoostClockFrequency, Power.Cap, SerialNumber, Model, and Version read byte-for-byte identical values before and after the refactor.\n\nPS8 references:\n- PropertyInfo struct: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/88572/8/src/nvidia-gpu/Inventory.hpp#42\n- addPropertyTarget helper: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/88572/8/src/nvidia-gpu/Inventory.cpp#138\n- for-loop replacing if/else: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/88572/8/src/nvidia-gpu/Inventory.cpp#366",
